  "prompt": "Whom was Muhammad worshipping before getting revelations?",
  "response": "Before receiving revelations, Muhammad was part of a polytheistic society in Mecca, where the predominant religious practices involved the worship of multiple deities. The Kaaba, a sacred site in Mecca, housed various idols representing different gods. However, Muhammad is said to have held a belief in one supreme god, often referred to as Allah, even before his prophetic mission began. His reflections on the nature of spirituality, the concept of a single God, and the practices of his society contributed to the foundational ideas he later developed in Islam after receiving revelations from the angel Gabriel.",
